The `myapp` CLI is the primary tool for developing, deploying, and managing Nhost projects. It lets you run your backend locally, manage configuration and infrastructure as code, link and deploy projects to Nhost Cloud, and provide AI assistants with access to your project through the built-in MCP server.

New here? Head over to [Quickstart](/getting-started/quickstart/cli) for CLI installation.

## Usage

```
myapp [GLOBAL OPTIONS] [command [COMMAND OPTIONS]] [ARGUMENTS...]
```

<div class="cli-reference">

---

## Global Options

| | |
| --- | --- |
| `--branch=""` | Git branch name. Detected from the current repo at `/path/to/repo` if unset. Default: `<current-git-branch>`. Env: `$MYAPP_BRANCH`. |
| `--help, -h` | show help. |
| `--root-folder=""` | Root folder of project. Default: `"."`. |
| `--verbose` | Enable verbose output. |


---

## Commands

---

<div class="cli-command cli-l0">

## config

</div>

<div class="cli-command cli-l1">

### `myapp config apply`

<div class="cli-body">

Apply config to `/etc/myapp` and send the `X-Config-Token` header.

| | |
| --- | --- |
| `--subdomain=""` | Subdomain to apply to. Env: `$MYAPP_SUBDOMAIN`. |
| `--yes` | Skip confirmation. |

</div>

</div>

---

<div class="cli-command cli-l0">

## dev

</div>

<div class="cli-command cli-l1">

### `myapp dev`

<div class="cli-body">

Start the development environment. *Aliases: `d`*

</div>

</div>

<div class="cli-command cli-l1">

### `myapp dev logs`

<div class="cli-body">

Show development logs.

</div>

</div>

